  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PeruTM9.11">
<l>ērārnta karuneṭumā lirāmaṉāy vaṉampukka vataṉuk kāṟṟā</l>
<l>tārārnta taṭavaraittōḷ ṭayarataṉṟāṉ pulampiyavap pulampal taṉṉaik</l>
<l>kūrārnta vēlvalavaṉ kōḻiyarkōṉ kuṭaikkulacē karaṉcoṟ ceyta</l>
<l>cīrārnta tamiḻmālai yivaivallār tīneṟikkaṭ cellār tāmē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Those who master</l>
<l>	these Tamil garlands filled with excellence, that lament</l>
<l rend="indent">- which Daśaratha, with large mountain[-like] shoulders bedecked with garlands,</l>
<l rend="indent">[uttered] lamentingly,</l>
<l rend="indent">as the dark tall Māl full of beauty [born] as Rāma entered the forest,</l>
<l rend="indent">being unconsolable about that -</l>
<l>put into words by Kulacēkaraṉ [who has] a [royal] parasol,</l>
<l rend="indent">the king of the Kōḻi people, capable [wielder of] a lance that is full of sharpness,</l>
<l>shall not go in the evil path.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
